        "paragraph_index": 0,
        "text": "Short answer: there isn’t a single “binding constant for DTPA.” DTPA (diethylenetriaminepentaacetic acid, a.k.a. pentetic acid) forms complexes with many metal ions, and the stability constant depends on the specific metal, complex stoichiometry (e.g., ML, MHL), temperature, ionic strength/medium, and pH (protonation state). In our attempt here, no SRD‑46 rows could be retrieved within the time budget because the metal/conditions were not specified and the initial name lookups returned no matches.",
